review:
[b]Melissa K. and the Heart of Gold Collector's Edition[/b] is a Hidden Object game that tells the story of a teacher named Melissa.
I'll tell you everything I could find out about the game:
[list]
[*] The game recreates various locations from reality.
[*] The game has wonderful graphics and cutscenes;
[*] The game shows a new kind of gameplay that I haven't seen anywhere else — the ability to look at one location from different angles;
[*] The game has achievements and cards;
[*] You can't get away from the game until the end;
[*] The game has puzzles not only of old genres, but also of new ones, in addition, some of the developers came up with themselves;
[*] The game has a wonderful soundtrack.
[/list]
In general, I liked the game, I recommend it!
